1531
01:07:38,320 --> 01:07:40,197
<i>(music slows and distorts)</i>

1532
01:07:40,240 --> 01:07:41,753
James, James, please!

1533
01:07:41,800 --> 01:07:43,677
Just stay away from the
hi-fi system, all right?

1534
01:07:43,720 --> 01:07:44,630
It's reel-to-reel.

1535
01:07:44,680 --> 01:07:46,113
You can't wind it like that.

1536
01:07:46,160 --> 01:07:48,037
<i>~</i> Don't ever set me free<i>... ~</i>

1537
01:07:48,080 --> 01:07:49,308
<i>(drink sloshes)</i>

1538
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:51,430
Christ! Terry!

1539
01:07:51,480 --> 01:07:52,708
This is Italian knit!

1540
01:07:52,760 --> 01:07:53,670
Watch where you're going!

1541
01:07:53,720 --> 01:07:55,073
It's just a shirt, man!

1542
01:07:55,120 --> 01:07:57,588
Frank! Come quick!

1543
01:07:57,640 --> 01:08:00,916
Lance just fell
into the conversation pit!

1544
01:08:05,640 --> 01:08:08,393
Excuse me, you know
where Lance Applebaum is?

1545
01:08:08,440 --> 01:08:10,112
Thank you.

1546
01:08:10,160 --> 01:08:12,754
DOCTOR:
These bottles need to be labeled
when you pick them up.

1547
01:08:12,800 --> 01:08:14,279
Do you understand
how dangerous this is?

1548
01:08:14,320 --> 01:08:15,992
Do you?

1549
01:08:16,040 --> 01:08:17,792
Don't stand there crying,
just nod your head

1550
01:08:17,840 --> 01:08:19,159
and tell me
you won't do it again.

1551
01:08:19,200 --> 01:08:20,997
Now dry up and get back to work.

1552
01:08:21,040 --> 01:08:23,474
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Dr. Blair, Dr. Blair

1553
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:24,635
Dr. Sherwood Blair.

1554
01:08:24,680 --> 01:08:28,309
<i>(gently)</i>:
Hey, hey... you okay?

1555
01:08:28,360 --> 01:08:30,794
<i>(sniffling)</i>:
He told me to pick up the blood,

1556
01:08:30,840 --> 01:08:33,115
so I did, but he never told me
to label it.

1557
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:35,037
Hey, it's okay.

1558
01:08:35,080 --> 01:08:37,196
Stop crying.

1559
01:08:37,240 --> 01:08:39,196
What's your name?

1560
01:08:39,240 --> 01:08:41,800
- Brenda.
- Brenda.

1561
01:08:41,840 --> 01:08:43,876
Brenda, I wouldn't worry
about it.

1562
01:08:43,920 --> 01:08:45,353
You know, these doctors

1563
01:08:45,400 --> 01:08:47,630
you know,
they don't know everything.

1564
01:08:47,680 --> 01:08:49,113
It's my first week

1565
01:08:49,160 --> 01:08:51,879
and I think they're
going to fire me.

1566
01:08:51,920 --> 01:08:55,196
No, no, nobody's
going to fire you, Brenda.

1567
01:08:55,240 --> 01:08:57,515
I bet you're good at your job.

1568
01:08:57,560 --> 01:08:59,471
No, I'm not.

1569
01:08:59,520 --> 01:09:02,830
Yeah, I bet if I asked you
to check on the status

1570
01:09:02,880 --> 01:09:04,791
of my friend Lance Applebaum

1571
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:07,229
that you could do that for me
in a second.

1572
01:09:07,280 --> 01:09:10,158
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Nurse Fitzsimmons to Recovery.

1573
01:09:10,200 --> 01:09:11,713
Nurse Fitzsimmons to Recovery.

1574
01:09:12,440 --> 01:09:15,000
Um...

1575
01:09:15,040 --> 01:09:17,873
Mr. Applebaum fractured
his ankle.

1576
01:09:17,920 --> 01:09:21,151
Dr. Ashland is treating him
in exam room seven.

1577
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:24,749
You see that? No problem.

1578
01:09:26,280 --> 01:09:28,794
This is the emergency chart.

1579
01:09:28,840 --> 01:09:30,239
See that blue star there?

1580
01:09:30,280 --> 01:09:32,953
That means that the patient
has been diagnosed.

1581
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:34,718
And then,
after he's been treated

1582
01:09:34,760 --> 01:09:38,196
we put a red circle here, see?

1583
01:09:38,240 --> 01:09:39,798
How do you like those braces?

1584
01:09:41,680 --> 01:09:43,750
I guess they're all right.

1585
01:09:43,800 --> 01:09:46,837
I got mine off last year.

1586
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:49,394
Boy, I hated them.
They were bottoms.

1587
01:09:49,440 --> 01:09:52,591
You know, I still got to wear
my mouth guard.

1588
01:09:52,640 --> 01:09:54,756
You have really nice teeth.

1589
01:09:55,760 --> 01:09:57,796
Well, thank you.

1590
01:09:57,840 --> 01:10:01,037
And you have a pretty smile.

1591
01:10:01,080 --> 01:10:02,832
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Custodial to cafeteria.

1592
01:10:02,880 --> 01:10:04,029
<i>(giggles)</i>

1593
01:10:04,080 --> 01:10:05,195
No, I mean it.

1594
01:10:05,240 --> 01:10:07,196
I really think
those braces look good on you.

1595
01:10:07,240 --> 01:10:09,117
Thank you.

1596
01:10:09,160 --> 01:10:11,355
You're welcome.

1597
01:10:13,880 --> 01:10:15,199
Brenda.

1598
01:10:15,240 --> 01:10:16,434
Yeah.

1599
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:19,358
Do you know if they're hiring
here at the hospital?

1600
01:10:20,680 --> 01:10:22,272
I'm not sure.

1601
01:10:22,320 --> 01:10:23,833
What do you want to do?

1602
01:10:23,880 --> 01:10:27,555
I'm a doctor.

1603
01:10:30,000 --> 01:10:31,592
FRANK:
<i>Dear Dad: </i>

1604
01:10:31,640 --> 01:10:33,870
<i>I've decided to get</i>
<i>off the road for awhile. </i>

1605
01:10:33,920 --> 01:10:36,150
<i>I've taken a night job</i>
<i>at a hospital</i>

1606
01:10:36,200 --> 01:10:37,872
<i>and met</i>
<i>some really nice people. </i>

1607
01:10:37,920 --> 01:10:39,956
<i>Feels good to have my feet</i>
<i>on the ground</i>

1608
01:10:40,000 --> 01:10:43,470
<i>to wake up in the same bed</i>
<i>every night. </i>

1609
01:10:43,520 --> 01:10:47,399
<i>Who knows, maybe I'll even find</i>
<i>someone to settle down with. </i>

1610
01:10:49,920 --> 01:10:51,876
Harvard Medical School...

1611
01:10:51,920 --> 01:10:54,150
top of your class.

1612
01:10:54,200 --> 01:10:57,158
Southern California
Children's Hospital.

1613
01:10:57,200 --> 01:11:00,715
Well, that's a pretty impressive
resume, Dr. Conners

1614
01:11:00,760 --> 01:11:03,832
but unfortunately, uh...
the only thing I need

1615
01:11:03,880 --> 01:11:07,111
is a...
an emergency room supervisor

1616
01:11:07,160 --> 01:11:10,072
for my midnight to 8:00am shift

1617
01:11:10,120 --> 01:11:14,272
someone to baby-sit
six interns and 20 nurses

1618
01:11:14,320 --> 01:11:17,073
but, uh...

1619
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:20,908
Hell, I doubt that, uh,
you would be interested in that.

1620
01:11:20,960 --> 01:11:22,757
Well, in the past

1621
01:11:22,800 --> 01:11:27,271
they've always let me choose
my own nurses.

1622
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:29,914
Dr. Connelly?

1623
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:31,109
Dr. Harris?

1624
01:11:31,160 --> 01:11:32,229
Present.

1625
01:11:32,280 --> 01:11:33,918
Dr. Ashland?

1626
01:11:33,960 --> 01:11:35,518
Dr. Conners...

1627
01:11:35,560 --> 01:11:37,755
You gonna take roll every night?

1628
01:11:37,800 --> 01:11:39,552
Uh, yes, I will, Dr. Ashland

1629
01:11:39,600 --> 01:11:43,354
and if you're going to be late,
I suggest you bring a note.

1630
01:11:43,400 --> 01:11:46,472
<i>(snickering)</i>

1631
01:11:46,520 --> 01:11:48,590
Miss Basmann.

1632
01:11:48,640 --> 01:11:50,312
Miss Mace.

1633
01:11:50,360 --> 01:11:51,873
Miss Strong.

1634
01:11:51,920 --> 01:11:53,273
Here.

1635
01:11:53,320 --> 01:11:55,356
Nurse Brown.

1636
01:11:55,400 --> 01:11:57,391
- Nurse Sanford?
- Here.

1637
01:11:57,440 --> 01:11:59,317
SURGEON <i>(on TV)</i>:
30 milligrams of codeine

1638
01:11:59,360 --> 01:12:00,270
every four hours.

1639
01:12:00,320 --> 01:12:01,833
Run the plasma
at 60 drops a minute

1640
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:03,757
until we calculate
the fluid requirements.

1641
01:12:03,800 --> 01:12:05,677
What do you estimate
the degree and extent

1642
01:12:05,720 --> 01:12:06,789
of the burns, Kildare?

1643
01:12:06,840 --> 01:12:08,398
DR. KILDARE:
Second and third-degree burns

1644
01:12:08,440 --> 01:12:10,078
over about 20 percent
of the body surface.

1645
01:12:10,120 --> 01:12:11,030
Do you concur?

1646
01:12:11,080 --> 01:12:11,990
I concur.

1647
01:12:12,040 --> 01:12:13,917
Let's get him up to Pediatrics.

1648
01:12:13,960 --> 01:12:17,316
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Nurse Hopp
to the Nurses' Station South.

1649
01:12:17,360 --> 01:12:19,999
Nurse Hopp
to the Nurses' Station South.

1650
01:12:20,040 --> 01:12:21,393
Hello, Brenda.

1651
01:12:21,440 --> 01:12:22,668
Hi, Dr. Conners.

1652
01:12:22,720 --> 01:12:24,631
You need to sign these.

1653
01:12:24,680 --> 01:12:26,591
Thank you.

1654
01:12:32,160 --> 01:12:34,310
Do you notice anything
different about me, Doctor?

1655
01:12:34,360 --> 01:12:35,793
- You got your braces off!
- Yeah!

1656
01:12:35,840 --> 01:12:37,114
Come here. Let me see.

1657
01:12:37,160 --> 01:12:39,037
I've been trying
to show you all night!

1658
01:12:39,080 --> 01:12:40,229
<i>(thunder rumbling)</i>

1659
01:12:40,280 --> 01:12:42,157
Wow. Good job.

1660
01:12:42,200 --> 01:12:43,679
Yeah?

1661
01:12:43,720 --> 01:12:45,358
So, did it hurt
when they took them off?

1662
01:12:45,400 --> 01:12:46,469
Mine felt so weird after.

1663
01:12:46,520 --> 01:12:48,511
Mm, I keep rubbing my tongue
over them.

1664
01:12:48,560 --> 01:12:50,312
I can't stop.
They're so slippery.

1665
01:12:50,360 --> 01:12:51,759
It feels good, though,
doesn't it?

1666
01:12:51,800 --> 01:12:53,711
Yeah, it feels incredible.

1667
01:12:55,400 --> 01:12:57,436
<i>(thunder rumbles)</i>

1668
01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:04,399
Oh, my.

1669
01:13:04,440 --> 01:13:06,795
I'm... I'm sorry.

1670
01:13:06,840 --> 01:13:08,751
<i>(thunder crashes)</i>

1671
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:10,711
<i>(passionate moaning)</i>

1672
01:13:17,800 --> 01:13:19,950
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Dr. Conners to the ER.

1673
01:13:20,000 --> 01:13:21,558
Dr. Conners to the ER.

1674
01:13:21,600 --> 01:13:22,715
Shouldn't you go?

1675
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:24,478
No. No, no.

1676
01:13:24,520 --> 01:13:26,431
They have a staff doctor
in the emergency ward.

1677
01:13:26,480 --> 01:13:28,391
We'll be fine.

1678
01:13:32,680 --> 01:13:35,717
<i>(panting)</i>:
What if he's in surgery?

1679
01:13:35,760 --> 01:13:38,797
Do you really think
I have to go?

1680
01:13:38,840 --> 01:13:41,354
Oh. In here, Dr. Conners.

1681
01:13:41,400 --> 01:13:43,311
<i>(child sobbing)</i>

1682
01:13:52,440 --> 01:13:54,829
<i>(sobbing)</i>

1683
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:00,879
Gentlemen, what, uh...
what seems to be the problem?

1684
01:14:00,920 --> 01:14:02,194
Bicycle accident.

1685
01:14:02,240 --> 01:14:06,119
Fractured tibia about
five inches below the patella.

1686
01:14:06,160 --> 01:14:08,071
Hmm.

1687
01:14:10,480 --> 01:14:12,471
- Dr. Harris.
- Yes?

1688
01:14:12,520 --> 01:14:13,509
Do you concur?

1689
01:14:13,560 --> 01:14:16,836
C... Concur with what, sir?

1690
01:14:16,880 --> 01:14:18,757
With what Dr. Ashland just said.

1691
01:14:18,800 --> 01:14:21,314
Do you... Do you concur?

1692
01:14:21,360 --> 01:14:23,555
Uh... well, it was
a bicycle accident.

1693
01:14:23,600 --> 01:14:25,431
Um, the boy told us.

1694
01:14:25,480 --> 01:14:26,959
So you concur?

1695
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:28,433
Concur? Uh...

1696
01:14:28,480 --> 01:14:30,198
I think we should take an X ray

1697
01:14:30,240 --> 01:14:32,879
then stitch him up
and put him in a walking cast.

1698
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:34,035
<i>(moans)</i>

1699
01:14:36,040 --> 01:14:38,156
That's very good, Dr. Ashland.
Very good.

1700
01:14:38,200 --> 01:14:40,839
Well, you don't seem
to have much need for me.

1701
01:14:40,880 --> 01:14:42,472
Carry on.

1702
01:14:44,280 --> 01:14:46,919
I blew it, didn't I?

1703
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:49,030
Why didn't I concur?

1704
01:14:49,080 --> 01:14:51,958
WOMAN <i>(over P.A.)</i>:
Dr. Henning, call extension 219.

1705
01:14:52,000 --> 01:14:53,479
Dr. Henning, extension 219.

1706
01:14:53,520 --> 01:14:55,431
<i>(vomiting)</i>

1707
01:15:03,560 --> 01:15:06,870
<i>(distant jackhammer drilling)</i>

1708
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:11,108
FRANK SR:
Make yourself at home!

1709
01:15:11,160 --> 01:15:13,993
Frank Abagnale Sr.

1710
01:15:14,040 --> 01:15:16,395
You're not a cop.

1711
01:15:16,440 --> 01:15:20,069
Special Agent Hanratty, FBI.

1712
01:15:20,120 --> 01:15:21,075
You're not a cop.

1713
01:15:21,120 --> 01:15:23,429
My landlord said
you were not a cop.

1714
01:15:23,480 --> 01:15:25,038
Well, if you're going
to arrest me

1715
01:15:25,080 --> 01:15:26,638
I'd like
to put on a different suit

1716
01:15:26,680 --> 01:15:27,795
if that's okay with you.

1717
01:15:27,840 --> 01:15:29,353
No, no, I'm not here
to arrest you.

1718
01:15:29,400 --> 01:15:31,356
I'm looking for your son.
He's in trouble.

1719
01:15:31,400 --> 01:15:32,753
Do you know where he is?

1720
01:15:35,480 --> 01:15:36,595
If I tell you where he is

1721
01:15:36,640 --> 01:15:38,517
will you promise
not to tell his mother?

1722
01:15:38,560 --> 01:15:40,232
Sure.

1723
01:15:40,280 --> 01:15:43,590
Frank made up a fake I.D.

1724
01:15:43,640 --> 01:15:44,993
and enlisted
in the Marine Corps.

1725
01:15:45,040 --> 01:15:46,393
He's over in Vietnam right now.

1726
01:15:46,440 --> 01:15:48,112
That kid is halfway
around the world

1727
01:15:48,160 --> 01:15:50,628
crawling through the damn jungle

1728
01:15:50,680 --> 01:15:52,955
fighting the Communists, so...

1729
01:15:53,000 --> 01:15:55,116
<i>(shuts refrigerator door)</i>

1730
01:15:55,160 --> 01:15:58,550
please, don't come to my home
and call my boy a criminal

1731
01:15:58,600 --> 01:15:59,919
because that kid has
more guts...

1732
01:15:59,960 --> 01:16:01,757
I never said he was a criminal,
Mr. Abagnale.

1733
01:16:01,800 --> 01:16:03,438
I said he was in trouble.

1734
01:16:03,480 --> 01:16:06,711
If you'd like to give me a call
and talk, here's my number.

1735
01:16:17,120 --> 01:16:18,599
<i>(pen scribbling)</i>

1736
01:16:18,640 --> 01:16:20,358
You're not a father, are you?

1737
01:16:22,440 --> 01:16:24,670
Pardon me?

1738
01:16:24,720 --> 01:16:26,119
If you were a father,
you'd know.

1739
01:16:26,160 --> 01:16:29,436
I would never give up my son.

1740
01:16:29,480 --> 01:16:32,995
I would never give up my son.

1741
01:16:33,040 --> 01:16:36,271
Yes, sir. I understand.

1742
01:16:36,320 --> 01:16:38,436
Sean, Sean, now get this:

1743
01:16:38,480 --> 01:16:39,833
"Riverbend Apartments

1744
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:43,190
415 Landover, Atlanta, Georgia."

1745
01:16:43,240 --> 01:16:44,593
Atlanta, Georgia.

1746
01:16:44,640 --> 01:16:46,198
Yeah, I'm on my way
to the airport.

1747
01:16:46,240 --> 01:16:48,196
I'll meet the team in, uh,
in four hours.

1748
01:16:48,240 --> 01:16:49,673
Bye-bye.

1749
01:16:51,840 --> 01:16:53,319
Come on, it's okay.

