through all this.

2783
02:05:45,840 --> 02:05:48,638
You go back to Europe, you're
gonna die in Perpignan Prison.

2784
02:05:48,680 --> 02:05:50,193
You try to run
here in the States

2785
02:05:50,240 --> 02:05:52,310
we'll send you
back to Atlanta for 50 years.

2786
02:05:52,360 --> 02:05:55,557
I know that.

2787
02:05:55,600 --> 02:05:57,955
I spent four years trying
to arrange your release.

2788
02:05:58,000 --> 02:05:59,672
Had to convince my bosses
at the FBI

2789
02:05:59,720 --> 02:06:01,915
and the Attorney General
of the United States

2790
02:06:01,960 --> 02:06:02,870
you wouldn't run.

2791
02:06:02,920 --> 02:06:05,673
Why'd you do it?

2792
02:06:05,720 --> 02:06:07,073
You're just a kid.

2793
02:06:07,120 --> 02:06:08,838
I'm not your kid.

2794
02:06:08,880 --> 02:06:11,155
You said you were
going to Chicago.

2795
02:06:11,200 --> 02:06:13,031
My daughter can't see me
this weekend.

2796
02:06:13,080 --> 02:06:14,957
She's going skiing.

2797
02:06:15,000 --> 02:06:16,558
You said she was four years old.

2798
02:06:16,600 --> 02:06:17,635
You're lying.

2799
02:06:17,680 --> 02:06:19,193
She was four when I left.

2800
02:06:19,240 --> 02:06:20,559
Now she's 15.

2801
02:06:20,600 --> 02:06:23,637
My wife's been remarried
for 11 years.

2802
02:06:23,680 --> 02:06:25,830
I see Grace every now and again.

2803
02:06:25,880 --> 02:06:27,757
I don't understand.

2804
02:06:27,800 --> 02:06:29,677
Sure you do.

2805
02:06:29,720 --> 02:06:32,280
Sometimes it's easier
living the lie.

2806
02:06:35,600 --> 02:06:38,433
I'm going to let you
fly tonight, Frank.

2807
02:06:38,480 --> 02:06:40,277
I'm not even going
to try to stop you.

2808
02:06:40,320 --> 02:06:42,550
That's 'cause I know
you'll be back on Monday.

2809
02:06:42,600 --> 02:06:45,751
Yeah? How do you know
I'll come back?

2810
02:06:45,800 --> 02:06:48,394
<i>(chuckles quietly)</i>

2811
02:06:48,440 --> 02:06:50,556
Look.

2812
02:06:50,600 --> 02:06:52,431
Frank...

2813
02:06:52,480 --> 02:06:54,675
nobody's chasing you.

